WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:55.630 --> 00:00:58.090
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

3
00:00:58.170 --> 00:00:59.880
Show me its arm.

4
00:00:59.969 --> 00:01:02.840
- She bears the mark.
- No!

5
00:01:05.509 --> 00:01:09.020
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

6
00:01:11.439 --> 00:01:13.560
- Help me!
- I can't.

7
00:01:13.650 --> 00:01:16.439
- They're going to kill her.

8
00:01:24.319 --> 00:01:28.870
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

9
00:01:37.379 --> 00:01:39.959
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

10
00:02:04.319 --> 00:02:06.819
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

11
00:02:06.909 --> 00:02:09.829
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

12
00:02:09.909 --> 00:02:14.750
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

13
00:02:14.830 --> 00:02:17.250
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

14
00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:20.710
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

15
00:02:20.759 --> 00:02:22.879
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

16
00:02:22.969 --> 00:02:25.050
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

17
00:02:25.129 --> 00:02:28.719
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

18
00:05:55.930 --> 00:05:57.930
Dada! Dada!

19
00:06:01.350 --> 00:06:04.649
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

20
00:06:05.899 --> 00:06:09.149
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

21
00:06:09.189 --> 00:06:11.149
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

22
00:06:11.189 --> 00:06:13.490
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

23
00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:21.040
Come on.

24
00:06:23.370 --> 00:06:26.420
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

25
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:29.420
But. Dada. it's a baby.

26
00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:34.300
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

27
00:06:34.379 --> 00:06:37.930
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

28
00:06:38.009 --> 00:06:40.350
Daikinis are big.

29
00:06:40.389 --> 00:06:43.519
- Giants who live far away.

30
00:06:43.600 --> 00:06:45.899
Oh. she's so cute.

31
00:06:45.980 --> 00:06:50.019
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

32
00:06:50.069 --> 00:06:55.319
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

33
00:06:55.399 --> 00:06:57.319
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

34
00:06:57.370 --> 00:07:01.540
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

35
00:07:01.620 --> 00:07:05.079
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

36
00:07:06.620 --> 00:07:10.459
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

37
00:07:10.550 --> 00:07:12.509
Baaa!

38
00:07:15.930 --> 00:07:19.430
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

39
00:07:19.509 --> 00:07:21.509
Where did you
get these seeds?

40
00:07:21.600 --> 00:07:24.350
Well. maybe I used magic.

41
00:07:24.430 --> 00:07:28.350
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

42
00:07:28.439 --> 00:07:32.019
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

43
00:07:32.069 --> 00:07:35.529
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

44
00:07:35.610 --> 00:07:38.660
- There's no law against that.

45
00:07:38.740 --> 00:07:43.910
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

46
00:07:43.949 --> 00:07:46.290
Magic?
You'll need magic...

47
00:07:46.370 --> 00:07:48.750
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

48
00:07:50.790 --> 00:07:56.300
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

49
00:07:58.509 --> 00:08:02.259
- Baaa-

50
00:08:05.389 --> 00:08:08.389
Oh. you're lovely.

51
00:08:08.439 --> 00:08:10.439
- Yes. you are.

52
00:08:10.519 --> 00:08:14.980
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

53
00:08:15.029 --> 00:08:19.949
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

54
00:08:20.029 --> 00:08:22.779
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

55
00:08:22.829 --> 00:08:27.579
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

56
00:08:27.660 --> 00:08:29.709
There we are. Come on.

57
00:08:29.790 --> 00:08:32.420
Hey. I will not be ignored!

58
00:08:32.500 --> 00:08:36.170
Mims? Ranon?

59
00:08:47.179 --> 00:08:49.309
- You're gonna be all clean.

60
00:08:55.980 --> 00:08:59.279
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

61
00:08:59.360 --> 00:09:01.950
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

62
00:09:02.029 --> 00:09:04.830
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

63
00:09:04.909 --> 00:09:07.830
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

64
00:09:07.870 --> 00:09:10.919
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

65
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:15.039
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

66
00:09:15.129 --> 00:09:17.169
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

67
00:09:17.259 --> 00:09:21.009
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

68
00:09:21.049 --> 00:09:24.350
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

69
00:09:27.100 --> 00:09:30.769
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

70
00:09:30.850 --> 00:09:33.649
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

71
00:09:41.279 --> 00:09:44.740
- Dada. she likes you.

72
00:09:51.750 --> 00:09:52.919
- Bye.

73
00:09:52.919 --> 00:09:56.039
- Bye.

74
00:09:56.090 --> 00:10:00.009
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

75
00:10:06.049 --> 00:10:09.639
I will now magic ally join the rings!

76
00:10:31.620 --> 00:10:34.210
- Whoa-ah!

77
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:41.419
Thank you. son.

78
00:10:41.460 --> 00:10:46.509
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

79
00:11:01.690 --> 00:11:03.950
Give me a ripe one. Good.

80
00:11:10.159 --> 00:11:14.659
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

81
00:11:14.750 --> 00:11:19.590
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

82
00:11:27.639 --> 00:11:32.769
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

83
00:11:32.850 --> 00:11:38.480
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

84
00:11:40.730 --> 00:11:43.149
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

85
00:11:45.860 --> 00:11:48.909
No!
Hey. come here. you!

86
00:11:53.330 --> 00:11:56.750
I had seen enough.

87
00:12:11.850 --> 00:12:15.139
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

88
00:12:15.220 --> 00:12:18.139
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

89
00:12:18.190 --> 00:12:21.649
Bring forth the hopefuls.

90
00:12:21.730 --> 00:12:24.149
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

91
00:12:24.230 --> 00:12:27.990
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

92
00:12:28.070 --> 00:12:30.529
Is this a joke?

93
00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:35.080
- Willow?

94
00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:42.960
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

95
00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:47.590
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

96
00:12:47.669 --> 00:12:51.679
All that your require
is your intuition.

97
00:12:51.759 --> 00:12:55.850
Now. the power
to control the world...

98
00:12:55.929 --> 00:13:00.440
is in which finger?

99
00:13:42.399 --> 00:13:46.940
- No apprentice this year!

100
00:14:07.340 --> 00:14:10.720
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

101
00:14:10.799 --> 00:14:13.720
Take Ranon in there. quick!

102
00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:24.559
- Mims!

103
00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:28.070
- Mims!

104
00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:41.159
- Mims!
- Dada-

105
00:14:42.409 --> 00:14:45.500
- I'm scared. Dada!

106
00:14:55.799 --> 00:14:58.389
Come on!

107
00:15:16.029 --> 00:15:18.990
- Vohnkar!

108
00:15:28.500 --> 00:15:31.419
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

109
00:15:33.759 --> 00:15:35.549
Dada! Dada!

110
00:15:38.889 --> 00:15:41.139
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

111
00:15:44.179 --> 00:15:47.980
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

112
00:15:55.360 --> 00:15:58.700
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

113
00:15:58.779 --> 00:16:01.779
- I'm here.

114
00:16:05.870 --> 00:16:09.500
- Oh. Kiaya.

115
00:16:09.580 --> 00:16:11.789
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

116
00:16:11.840 --> 00:16:14.710
We have to take her
to the village council.

117
00:16:28.190 --> 00:16:33.110
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

118
00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:35.570
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

119
00:16:35.649 --> 00:16:37.610
until they find what
they're looking for!

120
00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:40.950
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

121
00:16:41.029 --> 00:16:43.529
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

122
00:16:43.580 --> 00:16:48.710
- In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:48.789 --> 00:16:50.919
In the pit! In the pit!

124
00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:54.299
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

125
00:16:54.379 --> 00:16:58.720
- Willow Ufgood.

126
00:16:58.799 --> 00:17:01.259
Come forward.

127
00:17:06.929 --> 00:17:12.269
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

128
00:17:17.859 --> 00:17:20.029
- A Daikini child.

129
00:17:20.109 --> 00:17:23.319
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

130
00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:24.490
Yeah!

131
00:17:24.579 --> 00:17:27.869
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

132
00:17:27.950 --> 00:17:30.579
This child is special!

133
00:17:30.670 --> 00:17:34.960
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

134
00:17:35.039 --> 00:17:38.089
All the way across
the great river...

135
00:17:38.170 --> 00:17:40.259
to the Daikini crossroads.

136
00:17:40.339 --> 00:17:45.049
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

137
00:17:45.099 --> 00:17:48.470
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

138
00:17:48.559 --> 00:17:51.519
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

139
00:17:53.099 --> 00:17:55.730
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

140
00:17:55.769 --> 00:17:58.319
No!

141
00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:01.950
I will consult the bones!

142
00:18:09.329 --> 00:18:14.829
- The bones tell me... nothing.

143
00:18:16.500 --> 00:18:20.420
Do you have any love
for this child?

144
00:18:28.849 --> 00:18:33.309
Yes. Yes. I do.

145
00:18:33.390 --> 00:18:37.819
- The bones have spoken!

146
00:18:37.859 --> 00:18:41.819
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

147
00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:45.990
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

148
00:18:46.069 --> 00:18:48.579
But you will need help.

149
00:18:48.660 --> 00:18:54.000
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

150
00:18:56.039 --> 00:19:00.170
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

151
00:19:00.210 --> 00:19:03.509
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

152
00:19:03.589 --> 00:19:06.049
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

153
00:19:06.140 --> 00:19:08.849
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

154
00:19:08.890 --> 00:19:12.099
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

155
00:19:20.109 --> 00:19:22.690
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

156
00:19:22.779 --> 00:19:26.160
And according to the bones...

157
00:19:26.240 --> 00:19:29.619
- Bh-
-That leader is...

158
00:19:29.700 --> 00:19:31.119
...you. Burglekutt!

159
00:19:31.119 --> 00:19:32.119
you. Burglekutt!

160
00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:35.670
vohnkar!

161
00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:39.839
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

162
00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:45.220
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

163
00:19:45.299 --> 00:19:49.220
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

164
00:19:49.259 --> 00:19:53.720
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

165
00:19:53.809 --> 00:19:58.559
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

166
00:19:58.599 --> 00:20:01.230
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

167
00:20:01.319 --> 00:20:06.150
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

168
00:20:08.109 --> 00:20:13.119
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

169
00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:17.210
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

170
00:20:20.289 --> 00:20:23.500
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

171
00:20:36.430 --> 00:20:40.900
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

172
00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:45.230
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

173
00:20:47.240 --> 00:20:49.359
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

174
00:20:49.450 --> 00:20:52.369
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

175
00:20:52.450 --> 00:20:55.869
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

176
00:20:55.950 --> 00:20:59.579
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

177
00:20:59.619 --> 00:21:02.789
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

178
00:21:02.839 --> 00:21:04.420
Me too. Me too. Dada.

179
00:21:06.009 --> 00:21:11.339
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

180
00:21:14.430 --> 00:21:16.970
Good-bye. Dada.

181
00:21:19.019 --> 00:21:23.019
Go play!
Go on.

182
00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:30.529
We've never been apart.

183
00:21:31.569 --> 00:21:34.910
I miss you already.

184
00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:39.660
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

185
00:21:39.750 --> 00:21:41.670
I'll be back
before you know it.

186
00:21:43.920 --> 00:21:46.670
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

187
00:21:48.710 --> 00:21:51.430
And... here.

188
00:21:53.549 --> 00:21:56.349
This will bring you luck.

189
00:22:09.529 --> 00:22:11.859
Good brave people!

190
00:22:13.700 --> 00:22:16.450
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

191
00:22:16.529 --> 00:22:21.250
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

192
00:22:24.750 --> 00:22:28.339
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

193
00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:31.970
Going the direction the bird is flying!

194
00:22:32.049 --> 00:22:35.970
- Ooh.

195
00:22:36.049 --> 00:22:38.890
It's going back to the village!

196
00:22:40.730 --> 00:22:42.690
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

197
00:22:42.769 --> 00:22:45.019
Move out!

198
00:23:08.960 --> 00:23:12.420
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

199
00:23:12.509 --> 00:23:16.549
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

200
00:23:16.589 --> 00:23:19.099
- The baby's sick.

201
00:23:23.059 --> 00:23:27.650
She's not sick!
Let me see.

202
00:23:27.730 --> 00:23:30.940
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

203
00:23:33.529 --> 00:23:36.609
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

204
00:23:38.950 --> 00:23:40.619
Clean me up.

205
00:23:44.289 --> 00:23:47.500
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

206
00:23:47.579 --> 00:23:51.500
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

207
00:23:51.549 --> 00:23:53.759
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

208
00:23:55.720 --> 00:23:57.970
Ah. General Kael. at last.

209
00:23:58.049 --> 00:24:02.769
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

210
00:24:02.849 --> 00:24:06.559
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

211
00:24:06.640 --> 00:24:12.109
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

212
00:24:12.190 --> 00:24:14.150
that continues
somehow to elude her.

213
00:24:16.069 --> 00:24:18.029
The baby of the prophecy?

214
00:24:18.109 --> 00:24:21.529
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

215
00:24:21.619 --> 00:24:24.079
I must perform
the ritual that will...

216
00:24:24.160 --> 00:24:27.500
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

217
00:24:27.579 --> 00:24:30.329
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

218
00:24:30.380 --> 00:24:32.460
You'll do as I say. child.

219
00:24:38.890 --> 00:24:41.049
I read the signs.

220
00:24:41.140 --> 00:24:44.309
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

221
00:24:44.390 --> 00:24:48.559
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

222
00:25:04.289 --> 00:25:06.829
- Move!

223
00:25:06.910 --> 00:25:08.869
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

224
00:25:13.170 --> 00:25:16.880
- Come on!

225
00:25:26.470 --> 00:25:29.390
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

226
00:25:29.480 --> 00:25:32.440
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

227
00:25:32.519 --> 00:25:34.359
They couldn' t have gone far!

228
00:25:34.400 --> 00:25:37.400
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

229
00:25:44.779 --> 00:25:47.500
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

230
00:26:26.279 --> 00:26:30.450
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

231
00:26:46.890 --> 00:26:49.849
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

232
00:26:55.349 --> 00:26:57.859
- What was that?

233
00:26:59.190 --> 00:27:01.990
Get the spears!

234
00:27:18.420 --> 00:27:20.380
- Uhh. Uhh.

235
00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:24.299
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

236
00:27:24.380 --> 00:27:26.799
Do you understand?

237
00:27:26.890 --> 00:27:28.759
- Water.
- Yeah.

238
00:27:30.890 --> 00:27:32.890
Hurry up!

239
00:27:36.900 --> 00:27:39.819
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

240
00:27:39.900 --> 00:27:43.359
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

241
00:27:43.440 --> 00:27:45.859
We can't give her to him!

242
00:27:45.910 --> 00:27:49.869
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

243
00:27:49.950 --> 00:27:52.539
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

244
00:27:52.619 --> 00:27:55.500
He's looking right at us.

245
00:27:59.420 --> 00:28:01.420
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

246
00:28:01.460 --> 00:28:04.339
I'm somebody.

247
00:28:04.420 --> 00:28:08.759
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

248
00:28:10.599 --> 00:28:15.230
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

249
00:28:15.269 --> 00:28:19.230
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

250
00:28:19.309 --> 00:28:22.650
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

251
00:28:22.730 --> 00:28:26.109
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

252
00:28:26.150 --> 00:28:29.200
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

253
00:28:29.279 --> 00:28:34.369
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

254
00:28:34.450 --> 00:28:36.660
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

255
00:28:36.750 --> 00:28:40.170
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

256
00:28:40.250 --> 00:28:43.799
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

257
00:28:43.880 --> 00:28:47.799
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

258
00:28:47.880 --> 00:28:49.549
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

259
00:28:49.640 --> 00:28:51.720
Listen here. runt.

260
00:28:51.799 --> 00:28:55.769
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

261
00:28:55.849 --> 00:29:00.150
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

262
00:29:00.230 --> 00:29:03.609
You're gonna what?

263
00:29:07.490 --> 00:29:10.069
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

264
00:29:10.160 --> 00:29:12.160
Vohnkar. let's go!

265
00:29:15.829 --> 00:29:18.539
Meegosh. are you coming?

266
00:29:20.829 --> 00:29:24.420
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

267
00:29:24.500 --> 00:29:28.670
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

268
00:29:28.759 --> 00:29:31.430
just let me out of here.
Please!

269
00:29:31.509 --> 00:29:34.970
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

270
00:29:35.009 --> 00:29:37.309
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

271
00:29:37.349 --> 00:29:42.309
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

272
00:29:42.400 --> 00:29:47.190
- What'll we do now. Willow?

273
00:29:47.279 --> 00:29:49.900
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

274
00:29:49.990 --> 00:29:54.779
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

275
00:29:54.869 --> 00:29:58.619
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

276
00:29:58.700 --> 00:30:02.460
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

277
00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:08.380
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

278
00:30:08.460 --> 00:30:10.420
I'm really scared.

279
00:30:10.470 --> 00:30:13.339
No. don't! Don't!

280
00:30:13.390 --> 00:30:16.220
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

281
00:30:16.309 --> 00:30:18.980
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

282
00:30:19.059 --> 00:30:22.309
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

283
00:30:22.400 --> 00:30:24.940
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

284
00:30:53.549 --> 00:30:56.430
- What was that?

285
00:30:59.809 --> 00:31:03.519
Mornin'. boys.

286
00:31:03.599 --> 00:31:07.730
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

287
00:31:07.769 --> 00:31:11.150
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

288
00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:14.700
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

289
00:31:14.779 --> 00:31:17.740
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

290
00:31:17.779 --> 00:31:21.250
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

291
00:31:21.289 --> 00:31:23.460
Good.

292
00:31:28.210 --> 00:31:30.509
Stop! Wait!

293
00:31:32.259 --> 00:31:35.009
- Whoa!

294
00:31:40.470 --> 00:31:44.980
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

295
00:31:45.059 --> 00:31:47.559
I suppose you're a warrior.

296
00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:50.150
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

297
00:31:50.230 --> 00:31:53.069
Humph.

298
00:31:53.150 --> 00:31:56.910
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

299
00:32:06.619 --> 00:32:11.380
I don't know why I try.

300
00:32:16.180 --> 00:32:19.430
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

301
00:32:19.509 --> 00:32:21.430
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

302
00:32:21.509 --> 00:32:23.890
- What's that?

303
00:32:23.980 --> 00:32:27.940
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

304
00:32:28.019 --> 00:32:31.980
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

305
00:32:34.690 --> 00:32:38.490
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

306
00:32:42.829 --> 00:32:46.539
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

307
00:32:52.500 --> 00:32:56.420
- Everything's gonna be all right.

308
00:32:59.759 --> 00:33:02.849
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

309
00:33:04.809 --> 00:33:07.190
Uh. pardon me.

310
00:33:07.230 --> 00:33:09.349
Uh-

311
00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:20.200
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

312
00:33:20.279 --> 00:33:23.200
Will you please
take care of her?

313
00:33:23.279 --> 00:33:27.710
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

314
00:33:29.119 --> 00:33:32.289
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

315
00:33:32.380 --> 00:33:34.750
Well-

316
00:33:34.839 --> 00:33:39.380
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

317
00:33:39.470 --> 00:33:41.839
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

318
00:33:41.930 --> 00:33:43.759
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

319
00:33:43.849 --> 00:33:45.349
What are you doing this far north?

320
00:33:45.430 --> 00:33:47.430
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

321
00:33:48.430 --> 00:33:49.769
The castle?

322
00:33:49.809 --> 00:33:52.269
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

323
00:33:52.359 --> 00:33:54.269
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

324
00:33:54.359 --> 00:33:56.609
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

325
00:33:56.730 --> 00:34:01.029
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

326
00:34:01.109 --> 00:34:03.069
You serve no one.

327
00:34:03.160 --> 00:34:05.410
Remember?

328
00:34:05.490 --> 00:34:08.700
Sit in your coffin and rot.

329
00:34:08.789 --> 00:34:11.829
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

330
00:34:11.920 --> 00:34:14.340
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

331
00:34:14.420 --> 00:34:17.050
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

332
00:34:17.130 --> 00:34:19.219
and stick it
on a pig pole!

333
00:34:36.730 --> 00:34:41.449
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

334
00:34:45.449 --> 00:34:49.250
We're running out of food.

335
00:34:49.329 --> 00:34:52.960
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

336
00:34:53.000 --> 00:34:56.000
You know why?
Nobody cares.

337
00:34:58.880 --> 00:35:02.429
Except me.

338
00:35:02.510 --> 00:35:06.719
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

339
00:35:06.800 --> 00:35:10.769
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

340
00:35:10.849 --> 00:35:13.809
I believe he would. Willow.

341
00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:16.440
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

342
00:35:16.519 --> 00:35:21.739
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

343
00:35:21.820 --> 00:35:24.739
If I had somebody in my life.

344
00:35:24.820 --> 00:35:28.409
a little daughter. perhaps.

345
00:35:28.489 --> 00:35:31.750
I might have a reason
to go on living.

346
00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:37.789
You can't leave me
in here to die.

347
00:35:37.880 --> 00:35:40.920
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

348
00:35:54.230 --> 00:35:58.150
I feel better!

349
00:35:58.230 --> 00:36:01.940
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

350
00:36:02.030 --> 00:36:06.489
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

351
00:36:06.570 --> 00:36:11.579
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

352
00:36:11.659 --> 00:36:13.699
- Hee. hee. hee!

353
00:36:13.789 --> 00:36:18.670
- Wheee!

354
00:36:18.750 --> 00:36:22.000
She likes me.

355
00:36:24.090 --> 00:36:26.469
Here are her changing rags.

356
00:36:26.550 --> 00:36:28.760
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

357
00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:33.099
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

358
00:36:34.809 --> 00:36:38.349
- You wory too much. peck.

359
00:36:38.440 --> 00:36:42.360
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

360
00:36:42.440 --> 00:36:48.199
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

361
00:36:48.280 --> 00:36:51.659
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

362
00:36:58.170 --> 00:37:02.420
- Good-bye. little one.

363
00:37:11.139 --> 00:37:13.389
Please. take good care of her.

364
00:37:15.179 --> 00:37:18.019
I give you my word of honor!

365
00:37:24.690 --> 00:37:28.610
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

366
00:37:28.650 --> 00:37:32.909
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

367
00:37:32.989 --> 00:37:36.500
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

368
00:37:36.579 --> 00:37:38.829
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

369
00:37:38.920 --> 00:37:41.130
The heroes have come home."

370
00:37:41.210 --> 00:37:44.300
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

371
00:37:44.380 --> 00:37:48.630
- Yeah. Medals.

372
00:37:48.670 --> 00:37:52.429
Meegosh-

373
00:37:54.309 --> 00:37:58.429
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

374
00:37:58.519 --> 00:38:02.809
- There's nothing to wory about.

375
00:38:05.820 --> 00:38:08.110
Hyah! Ha!

376
00:38:08.190 --> 00:38:13.409
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

377
00:38:13.489 --> 00:38:17.250
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

378
00:38:17.329 --> 00:38:19.289
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

379
00:38:19.369 --> 00:38:22.539
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

380
00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:28.590
- Ah!
- Ow!

381
00:38:28.670 --> 00:38:32.340
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

382
00:38:32.429 --> 00:38:35.760
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

383
00:38:36.760 --> 00:38:40.519
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

384
00:38:41.809 --> 00:38:43.860
We'll outrun 'em!

385
00:38:48.610 --> 00:38:52.699
-Hey. ugly. wake up!-

386
00:38:52.780 --> 00:38:55.239
Huh?

387
00:38:55.280 --> 00:39:00.409
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

388
00:39:00.449 --> 00:39:03.250
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

389
00:39:03.289 --> 00:39:05.250
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

390
00:39:05.289 --> 00:39:06.710
All right. you heard her!

391
00:39:06.789 --> 00:39:10.590
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

392
00:39:10.630 --> 00:39:13.010
You are mine to toy with.

393
00:39:13.090 --> 00:39:16.599
Forward!

394
00:39:16.679 --> 00:39:20.469
- Gimme the rope.

395
00:39:20.559 --> 00:39:24.559
Where-
Where...

396
00:39:24.650 --> 00:39:26.940
did you get that baby?

397
00:39:26.980 --> 00:39:31.739
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

398
00:39:31.900 --> 00:39:35.070
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

399
00:39:35.110 --> 00:39:39.409
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

400
00:39:39.489 --> 00:39:41.579
Ahh-

401
00:39:43.829 --> 00:39:45.789
- Yaah!

402
00:39:50.050 --> 00:39:53.300
- You!

403
00:39:53.340 --> 00:39:58.429
Welcome to my kingdom.

404
00:40:04.599 --> 00:40:09.110
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

405
00:40:09.190 --> 00:40:12.440
Blora Danan told me.

406
00:40:12.489 --> 00:40:15.820
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

407
00:40:18.619 --> 00:40:24.159
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

408
00:40:24.250 --> 00:40:29.590
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

409
00:40:29.670 --> 00:40:34.590
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

410
00:40:34.670 --> 00:40:39.429
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

411
00:40:40.849 --> 00:40:45.809
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

412
00:40:45.889 --> 00:40:49.480
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

413
00:40:49.559 --> 00:40:53.820
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

414
00:40:53.860 --> 00:40:56.989
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

415
00:40:57.030 --> 00:41:00.829
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

416
00:41:00.989 --> 00:41:04.250
Blora. you don't want me.

417
00:41:04.329 --> 00:41:08.039
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

418
00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:13.630
Hello?

419
00:41:20.969 --> 00:41:24.389
Blora Danan must survive!

420
00:41:24.429 --> 00:41:29.309
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

421
00:41:29.349 --> 00:41:32.230
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

422
00:41:32.269 --> 00:41:36.650
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

423
00:41:36.690 --> 00:41:41.280
of your village.
your children- everyone.

424
00:41:45.949 --> 00:41:49.460
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

425
00:41:49.539 --> 00:41:54.750
The choice is yours.

426
00:42:17.320 --> 00:42:21.570
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

427
00:42:21.610 --> 00:42:25.869
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

428
00:42:28.449 --> 00:42:32.000
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

429
00:42:32.079 --> 00:42:36.630
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

430
00:42:36.710 --> 00:42:40.170
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

431
00:42:40.260 --> 00:42:42.889
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

432
00:42:42.969 --> 00:42:45.889
I hope so.

433
00:42:45.969 --> 00:42:49.559
Listen. be careful.

434
00:42:55.650 --> 00:43:00.190
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

435
00:43:00.280 --> 00:43:03.739
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

436
00:43:03.820 --> 00:43:08.289
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

437
00:43:08.369 --> 00:43:11.460
- She's what?
- Exiled...

438
00:43:11.539 --> 00:43:15.380
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

439
00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:18.090
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

440
00:43:18.170 --> 00:43:20.760
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

441
00:43:20.840 --> 00:43:23.130
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

442
00:43:23.179 --> 00:43:25.849
So?

443
00:43:25.929 --> 00:43:28.719
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

444
00:43:28.809 --> 00:43:31.429
Don't play with that wand.

445
00:43:31.480 --> 00:43:34.059
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

446
00:43:34.150 --> 00:43:36.610
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

447
00:43:36.690 --> 00:43:39.440
-Not a stupid peck like you.

448
00:43:39.480 --> 00:43:42.650
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

449
00:43:42.739 --> 00:43:45.030
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

450
00:43:45.110 --> 00:43:47.619
- This way.
- This way?

451
00:43:47.699 --> 00:43:51.449
- That's what I said.
- This way.

452
00:43:51.500 --> 00:43:54.960
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

453
00:43:55.039 --> 00:43:57.750
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

454
00:44:08.179 --> 00:44:12.349
- Take it up!

455
00:44:13.849 --> 00:44:18.110
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

456
00:44:18.190 --> 00:44:23.030
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

457
00:44:23.110 --> 00:44:26.699
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

458
00:45:04.440 --> 00:45:06.900
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

459
00:45:06.949 --> 00:45:09.909
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

460
00:45:09.989 --> 00:45:11.869
Get out of here. peck!

461
00:45:11.949 --> 00:45:14.289
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

462
00:45:27.679 --> 00:45:31.599
Ooh. look at her!

463
00:45:31.639 --> 00:45:33.929
I could use
a love potion on her!

464
00:45:33.969 --> 00:45:37.809
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

465
00:45:37.889 --> 00:45:39.599
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

466
00:45:39.690 --> 00:45:43.070
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

467
00:45:47.239 --> 00:45:49.239
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

468
00:45:56.199 --> 00:45:59.960
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

469
00:46:02.250 --> 00:46:07.380
You are so beautiful!

470
00:46:07.469 --> 00:46:11.090
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

471
00:46:11.179 --> 00:46:13.800
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

472
00:46:13.889 --> 00:46:15.639
That dust of broken heart!

473
00:46:30.489 --> 00:46:32.699
Beer!

474
00:46:35.829 --> 00:46:37.949
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

475
00:46:42.539 --> 00:46:44.539
Hurry! Hurry!

476
00:46:44.630 --> 00:46:46.500
My husband's coming!

477
00:46:46.590 --> 00:46:48.630
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

478
00:46:48.710 --> 00:46:51.340
- How do I look?
- Not you!

479
00:46:52.550 --> 00:46:54.469
Where the hell
did you come from?

480
00:46:54.550 --> 00:46:56.809
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

481
00:46:56.849 --> 00:47:00.690
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

482
00:47:00.769 --> 00:47:02.980
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

483
00:47:03.059 --> 00:47:06.690
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

484
00:47:06.730 --> 00:47:09.570
Whoa!

485
00:47:09.650 --> 00:47:12.239
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

486
00:47:12.320 --> 00:47:14.699
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

487
00:47:14.739 --> 00:47:17.159
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

488
00:47:17.239 --> 00:47:19.500
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

489
00:47:19.539 --> 00:47:21.659
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

490
00:47:21.750 --> 00:47:24.500
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

491
00:47:24.579 --> 00:47:26.420
- How do you do?

492
00:47:26.500 --> 00:47:28.880
Hilda! Ooh.

493
00:47:28.920 --> 00:47:31.050
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

494
00:47:31.130 --> 00:47:33.760
- Hey! Give her back!

495
00:47:33.840 --> 00:47:36.219
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

496
00:47:36.300 --> 00:47:39.219
- They get too excited.

497
00:47:39.269 --> 00:47:41.889
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

498
00:47:41.980 --> 00:47:44.019
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

499
00:47:44.099 --> 00:47:48.730
- Stop. please. Ooh.

500
00:47:48.820 --> 00:47:50.690
Come on.
Fight like a man!

501
00:47:50.739 --> 00:47:53.780
- Want to breed?

502
00:47:53.860 --> 00:47:56.869
Tempting. but no.

503
00:47:59.789 --> 00:48:01.750
Thank you.
Time to leave.

504
00:48:01.789 --> 00:48:03.750
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

505
00:48:03.789 --> 00:48:06.960
- Hey! Come along!

506
00:48:07.039 --> 00:48:09.630
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

507
00:48:09.710 --> 00:48:12.420
Gather pall these babies.

508
00:48:12.510 --> 00:48:14.760
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

509
00:48:18.510 --> 00:48:20.639
That's not the one.

510
00:48:24.349 --> 00:48:27.099
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

511
00:48:27.190 --> 00:48:29.769
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

512
00:48:29.860 --> 00:48:31.440
No! Don't let her!

513
00:48:31.530 --> 00:48:32.989
Aah!

514
00:48:33.070 --> 00:48:35.949
I gave you an order. woman!

515
00:48:45.289 --> 00:48:48.750
You-
You're... beautiful.

516
00:48:48.840 --> 00:48:52.170
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

517
00:48:54.760 --> 00:48:57.260
You're no woman!

518
00:48:57.340 --> 00:48:59.179
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

519
00:48:59.260 --> 00:49:02.139
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

520
00:49:02.179 --> 00:49:04.980
- Meet Llug.

521
00:49:06.269 --> 00:49:08.309
- After them!
- Out of the way!

522
00:49:14.610 --> 00:49:15.860
- To the horses!

523
00:49:15.860 --> 00:49:16.949
- To the horses!

524
00:49:19.489 --> 00:49:21.949
Hey! What are you doing?

525
00:49:26.329 --> 00:49:28.250
- Hyah!

526
00:49:28.329 --> 00:49:32.250
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

527
00:49:35.719 --> 00:49:40.599
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

528
00:49:40.679 --> 00:49:43.059
Don't let them get away!

529
00:49:44.719 --> 00:49:48.139
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

530
00:49:59.949 --> 00:50:01.989
Hyah!

531
00:50:07.119 --> 00:50:09.619
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

532
00:50:11.670 --> 00:50:15.340
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

533
00:50:38.739 --> 00:50:41.070
Madmartigan!
Stop!

534
00:51:11.139 --> 00:51:13.190
Franjean. help me!

535
00:51:17.820 --> 00:51:19.739
- Rool!
- Help!

536
00:51:19.820 --> 00:51:22.860
Rool! Rool.

537
00:51:24.030 --> 00:51:27.829
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

538
00:51:33.210 --> 00:51:35.460
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

539
00:51:35.539 --> 00:51:38.000
Yeah. pull!

540
00:51:56.190 --> 00:51:58.190
You can't have her!

541
00:52:04.110 --> 00:52:05.820
Whoa!

542
00:52:10.539 --> 00:52:14.119
- Rool. this isn't funny!

543
00:52:14.210 --> 00:52:16.130
Help me cut the rope!

544
00:52:29.309 --> 00:52:32.059
Who-oa!

545
00:52:53.579 --> 00:52:56.170
Willow. stay down!

546
00:52:59.880 --> 00:53:01.920
Whoa!

547
00:53:01.960 --> 00:53:04.219
Whoa!

548
00:53:04.300 --> 00:53:06.219
Gone crazy?

549
00:53:06.300 --> 00:53:08.429
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

550
00:53:08.510 --> 00:53:10.929
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

551
00:53:10.969 --> 00:53:13.599
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

552
00:53:36.409 --> 00:53:38.920
Whoa! Whoa!

553
00:53:42.090 --> 00:53:44.420
- Oh. Rool.

554
00:53:44.510 --> 00:53:48.179
Now we stop. peck.

555
00:53:48.260 --> 00:53:53.559
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

556
00:53:53.599 --> 00:53:57.809
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

557
00:53:59.309 --> 00:54:01.809
I just saved that infant's life!

558
00:54:03.269 --> 00:54:05.610
Hah! Hah!

559
00:54:05.690 --> 00:54:07.650
Gather your wits. Come on.

560
00:54:07.699 --> 00:54:10.739
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

561
00:54:11.820 --> 00:54:13.989
- Get down!

562
00:54:14.079 --> 00:54:16.449
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

563
00:54:18.369 --> 00:54:20.460
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

564
00:54:36.969 --> 00:54:39.559
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

565
00:54:39.639 --> 00:54:41.099
Before those troops come back.

566
00:54:41.150 --> 00:54:44.610
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

567
00:54:53.030 --> 00:54:55.119
Madmartigan. wait!

568
00:54:55.159 --> 00:54:58.500
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

569
00:54:58.579 --> 00:55:00.539
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

570
00:55:00.619 --> 00:55:03.840
My help? What do you need my help for?

571
00:55:03.920 --> 00:55:06.090
You're a sorcerer!

572
00:55:06.170 --> 00:55:09.380
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

573
00:55:09.469 --> 00:55:12.340
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

574
00:55:12.429 --> 00:55:15.679
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

575
00:55:18.929 --> 00:55:23.860
- Hurry! Big dogs!

576
00:55:23.940 --> 00:55:28.190
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

577
00:55:28.230 --> 00:55:30.190
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

578
00:55:44.380 --> 00:55:47.210
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

579
00:55:48.710 --> 00:55:52.340
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

580
00:55:53.380 --> 00:55:56.550
That way.

581
00:55:56.599 --> 00:56:00.219
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

582
00:56:00.309 --> 00:56:02.230
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

583
00:56:02.309 --> 00:56:04.519
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

584
00:56:04.599 --> 00:56:06.610
That way!

585
00:56:09.650 --> 00:56:14.199
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

586
00:56:14.239 --> 00:56:17.239
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

587
00:56:17.329 --> 00:56:19.539
But that's it!

588
00:56:19.579 --> 00:56:23.369
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

589
00:56:23.409 --> 00:56:28.590
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

590
00:56:28.670 --> 00:56:31.300
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

591
00:56:38.010 --> 00:56:42.679
Kael. have you found the child?

592
00:56:42.769 --> 00:56:44.519
The search goes on. my queen.

593
00:56:45.599 --> 00:56:47.610
Why. with my powers.

594
00:56:47.690 --> 00:56:50.900
with the strength
of my great army.

595
00:56:50.980 --> 00:56:54.400
can you not find
one little child?

596
00:56:54.449 --> 00:56:56.780
We look even now.
It won't be long.

597
00:56:56.860 --> 00:57:00.239
Find the child.
Find the child!

598
00:57:00.280 --> 00:57:02.909
Time is running out.

599
00:57:07.079 --> 00:57:11.500
- Good night.

600
00:57:11.550 --> 00:57:14.880
She is kinda cute.

601
00:57:14.969 --> 00:57:16.719
When she's quiet.

602
00:57:18.139 --> 00:57:20.050
She's really a princess.

603
00:57:20.139 --> 00:57:24.139
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

604
00:57:24.230 --> 00:57:26.139
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

605
00:57:26.230 --> 00:57:30.019
Go to sleep. Willow.

606
00:57:30.110 --> 00:57:32.610
Good night. Madmartigan.

607
00:57:32.650 --> 00:57:35.650
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

608
00:57:35.699 --> 00:57:39.030
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

609
00:57:39.119 --> 00:57:42.030
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

610
00:57:52.840 --> 00:57:55.550
Tuatha...

611
00:57:55.630 --> 00:57:57.800
Lawkathok...

612
00:57:57.880 --> 00:57:59.800
- Tuatha!

613
00:57:59.840 --> 00:58:02.599
Huh?
Willow?

614
00:58:03.679 --> 00:58:05.809
Willow?

615
00:58:07.559 --> 00:58:10.019
Oh. There you are.

616
00:58:10.099 --> 00:58:12.059
Madmartigan!

617
00:58:12.150 --> 00:58:15.480
'Night. Willow.

618
00:58:27.579 --> 00:58:29.579
This way! This way!

619
00:58:41.389 --> 00:58:43.349
What are you doing?

620
00:58:43.389 --> 00:58:45.769
I found some black root.
She loves it!

621
00:58:45.849 --> 00:58:48.769
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

622
00:58:48.849 --> 00:58:50.849
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

623
00:58:51.019 --> 00:58:54.070
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

624
00:58:54.150 --> 00:58:56.690
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

625
00:58:56.780 --> 00:58:59.530
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

626
00:58:59.623 --> 00:59:02.583
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

627
00:59:02.623 --> 00:59:04.962
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

628
00:59:09.132 --> 00:59:11.172
Did you see what he did?

629
00:59:11.262 --> 00:59:14.512
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

630
00:59:19.353 --> 00:59:22.692
- There it is! The island!

631
00:59:24.902 --> 00:59:26.813
We made it.

632
00:59:26.902 --> 00:59:31.442
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

633
00:59:31.532 --> 00:59:35.782
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

634
00:59:53.842 --> 00:59:55.842
Well. looks like
I got you here.

635
00:59:55.932 --> 00:59:58.392
You!
What did you do?

636
00:59:58.472 --> 01:00:01.472
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

637
01:00:01.563 --> 01:00:03.522
I found a boat.
We're all set.

638
01:00:03.603 --> 01:00:07.522
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

639
01:00:07.612 --> 01:00:10.942
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

640
01:00:13.032 --> 01:00:15.702
Your mother was lizard!

641
01:00:18.702 --> 01:00:21.202
- Good-bye. Sticks.

642
01:00:23.873 --> 01:00:26.792
If you really are a princess.

643
01:00:26.873 --> 01:00:29.842
take care of him.

644
01:00:36.182 --> 01:00:39.472
- Madmartigan!
- What?

645
01:00:39.552 --> 01:00:41.432
Thanks.

646
01:00:50.942 --> 01:00:53.482
Hey! Aah!

647
01:00:53.532 --> 01:00:56.902
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

648
01:00:58.072 --> 01:01:01.083
- It's all right. Blora.

649
01:01:01.162 --> 01:01:03.583
- Go to sleep.

650
01:01:03.662 --> 01:01:06.002
- Nobody'll find you here.

651
01:01:06.083 --> 01:01:07.672
I'll be back with
Fin Raziel very soon.

652
01:01:07.712 --> 01:01:11.042
We will guard her
with our meager lives.

653
01:01:39.362 --> 01:01:42.202
Raziel!

654
01:01:42.282 --> 01:01:46.083
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

655
01:01:50.002 --> 01:01:52.592
Raziel!

656
01:01:57.422 --> 01:02:01.092
She's not here.

657
01:02:04.103 --> 01:02:06.022
- Aah!

658
01:02:06.103 --> 01:02:09.642
Get back! Who are you?

659
01:02:10.772 --> 01:02:13.652
Who are you?

660
01:02:16.072 --> 01:02:19.152
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

661
01:02:19.242 --> 01:02:22.912
I've come to find the great
sorceress. Fin Raziel.

662
01:02:22.992 --> 01:02:25.583
That's me!
I'm Raziel!

663
01:02:27.623 --> 01:02:29.542
This can't be right!

664
01:02:29.623 --> 01:02:33.132
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

665
01:02:35.422 --> 01:02:38.012
Believe me. it could
have been worse!

666
01:02:38.092 --> 01:02:43.892
Oh. Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

667
01:02:43.972 --> 01:02:48.472
Then the prophecy is true.
The princess has been born.

668
01:02:48.563 --> 01:02:50.522
Take me to her.

669
01:02:53.063 --> 01:02:55.822
It is Blora Danan.

670
01:02:55.902 --> 01:02:58.822
Isn't she beautiful?

671
01:02:58.902 --> 01:03:01.862
Isn't she beautiful?

672
01:03:01.952 --> 01:03:05.452
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know. I-

673
01:03:05.532 --> 01:03:07.792
I expected something
more grand. Less. uh-

674
01:03:07.833 --> 01:03:09.792
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy!

675
01:03:09.873 --> 01:03:13.672
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

676
01:03:13.752 --> 01:03:17.092
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

677
01:03:18.302 --> 01:03:20.802
Yes. Sort a.

678
01:03:20.882 --> 01:03:23.382
-I'm a farmer.

679
01:03:23.472 --> 01:03:25.392
But I do know a few tricks.

680
01:03:25.432 --> 01:03:30.982
Tricks? Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.

681
01:03:31.103 --> 01:03:35.152
- Horses! Horses!

682
01:03:35.232 --> 01:03:37.732
Quick! Take her!
Hurry! Hurry!

683
01:03:46.532 --> 01:03:49.492
I knew he was a traitor!

684
01:03:52.083 --> 01:03:54.792
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut!

685
01:03:55.833 --> 01:03:58.632
Told you we'd find him
without your help.

686
01:03:58.712 --> 01:04:00.672
- Give me that baby.
- No!

687
01:04:04.132 --> 01:04:08.103
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

688
01:04:14.022 --> 01:04:15.902
This is the one
we're looking for.

689
01:04:15.982 --> 01:04:19.362
- We must take it back to Nockmaar.

690
01:04:22.152 --> 01:04:24.072
Lose your skirt?

691
01:04:31.742 --> 01:04:33.702
I've still got what counts.

692
01:04:33.752 --> 01:04:36.083
Not for long.

693
01:04:41.922 --> 01:04:45.472
- Bring him.
- Over here!

694
01:05:03.152 --> 01:05:05.902
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

695
01:05:05.952 --> 01:05:07.912
Then we will
have to track them.

696
01:05:07.952 --> 01:05:09.373
That would take forever.

697
01:05:09.452 --> 01:05:12.202
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us.

698
01:05:12.242 --> 01:05:15.452
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

699
01:05:15.542 --> 01:05:17.502
Are you suggesting
we go home?

700
01:05:17.583 --> 01:05:20.502
- Nah. This is more fun!
- All right.

701
01:05:20.592 --> 01:05:22.502
Fine. then.
Come on!

702
01:05:36.313 --> 01:05:39.772
I'm worried about Blora.
She doesn't sound good.

703
01:05:39.813 --> 01:05:42.612
Hurry! Practice
the chant I taught you!

704
01:05:42.652 --> 01:05:48.452
- Tanna... looatha- Oh. I can't
remember the middle part.

705
01:05:48.532 --> 01:05:50.572
Locktwaar!

706
01:05:50.623 --> 01:05:53.623
That's the word
that pleads for change.

707
01:05:53.702 --> 01:05:55.662
Locktwaar.

708
01:05:59.333 --> 01:06:02.502
Blora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

709
01:06:02.592 --> 01:06:04.502
Please. let me
take care of her.

710
01:06:04.592 --> 01:06:06.712
I don't need help
from a peck.

711
01:06:10.472 --> 01:06:14.512
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

712
01:06:14.603 --> 01:06:16.972
I'd like to break it.

713
01:06:17.022 --> 01:06:21.902
You may find that difficult while
I'm up here and you're down there.

714
01:06:25.022 --> 01:06:27.242
I hate that woman.

715
01:06:59.892 --> 01:07:01.982
Hyah!

716
01:07:05.772 --> 01:07:08.572
- I found it. Kael.

717
01:07:09.692 --> 01:07:12.742
That should make
my mother happy.

718
01:07:12.822 --> 01:07:15.833
What are they gonna do to her?

719
01:07:28.382 --> 01:07:31.052
Hither walha...

720
01:07:31.132 --> 01:07:34.682
bairn derubordak...

721
01:07:34.762 --> 01:07:36.682
- bellanockt.

722
01:07:36.762 --> 01:07:39.642
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

723
01:07:39.722 --> 01:07:42.942
- It's the life spark. It forms after-
- Well. it stinks!

724
01:07:43.022 --> 01:07:46.192
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

725
01:07:46.272 --> 01:07:49.282
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

726
01:07:49.362 --> 01:07:52.452
- If only you'd quit talking about it.

727
01:07:52.532 --> 01:07:55.912
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

728
01:07:55.952 --> 01:07:58.782
But. Raziel.
I'm not ready yet.

729
01:07:58.873 --> 01:08:02.083
You'd better be.
Get me down.

730
01:08:05.712 --> 01:08:08.132
Ow!

731
01:08:10.762 --> 01:08:13.762
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

732
01:08:13.842 --> 01:08:16.592
Muskrat!
When I change back...

733
01:08:16.642 --> 01:08:20.603
to my former self.
I will crush this army.

734
01:08:20.682 --> 01:08:23.353
and take Blora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

735
01:08:23.432 --> 01:08:26.023
where she will be safe.

736
01:08:26.103 --> 01:08:28.443
- Ow!

737
01:08:28.483 --> 01:08:30.443
What'd you bite me for?

738
01:08:30.483 --> 01:08:33.823
